Class SequentialBatchProcessor

Sequential Batch Processor

Core processor for intelligent pair-based batching with auto-chaining. Handles request chaining, array expansion, and tier-based optimization.

Example

Basic usage:
const processor = new SequentialBatchProcessor({ debug: true });

const result = await processor.processBatch(
  [
    { method: 'getSignaturesForAddress', params: [address] },
    { method: 'getTransaction', inputFrom: 0, inputPath: '[].signature', expandArray: true }
  ],
  async (method, params) => {
    // Your RPC executor
    return await rpcClient.call(method, params);
  }
);

console.log(`Quota Cost: ${result.metadata.quotaCost}`);
console.log(`RPC Calls: ${result.metadata.actualRpcCalls}`);
console.log(`Results:`, result.results);

processBatch

  • processBatch(input, executor): Promise<SequentialBatchResponse<any>>

  • Process Sequential Batch

    Main entry point for processing sequential batch requests with auto-chaining. Handles validation, execution, and metadata collection.

    Parameters

    • input: SequentialBatchInput

      Single pair or array of pairs to process

    • executor: ((method: string, params: any[]) => Promise<any>)

      RPC executor function (method, params) => Promise

        • (method, params): Promise<any>

        • Parameters

          • method: string
          • params: any[]

          Returns Promise<any>

    Returns Promise<SequentialBatchResponse<any>>

    Promise with complete response including results, metadata, and errors

    Throws

    Error if validation fails or execution encounters fatal errors

    Example

    Process single pair:
    const result = await processor.processBatch(
      [
        { method: 'getSignaturesForAddress', params: [address, { limit: 10 }] },
        { method: 'getTransaction', inputFrom: 0, inputPath: '[].signature', expandArray: true }
      ],
      async (method, params) => await client.call(method, params)
    );

    Example

    Process multiple pairs in parallel:
    const result = await processor.processBatch(
      [
        [req1, req2],
        [req3, req4]
      ],
      executor
    );
